			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I dunno, unless you have a haste item I would take a Mith 2-hander over this, by virtue of it bieng 10 dly faster.  I generally consider 1 dmg=2.5 dly, so M2, bieng 4 dmg and 10 dly less than Skarlon, is equal, but better because the speed adds a slight difference that grows as the battle stretches out.  M2 is better IMO for paladins and SK's, as warriors are more concerned with damage, as they get higher multipliers.  It's really your call, if you have a FBSS or, better yet, CoF or RBB, use this over M2.  Otherwise, M2 an TBB seems the way to go.  Just my preferance.  Once you get to the planes, drop this like a rock for a Monsoon/Sunderfury/Bloodmoon/Ob. Claymore/Darkmetal/FA/etc
